OL,3,CSeveral children detained in police
OL,4,Ccustody for too long, inspectors find
OL,6,FThe aim of the joint inspection was to
OL,7,Fassess the treatment of, and
OL,8,Fconditions for, individuals detained
OL,9,Fat the three primary custody centres
OL,10,Fin Glasgow.
OL,12,FCraig Naylor, HM Chief Inspector of
OL,13,FConstabulary in Scotland, has called
OL,14,Fon Police Scotland to ensure decisions
OL,15,Finvolving children in police custody
OL,16,Fare subject to "robust management
OL,17,Foversight".
OL,19,FHe has also recommended Police
OL,20,FScotland make sure such decisions are
OL,21,Frecorded appropriately.
