OL,3,CSeveral children detained in police
OL,4,Ccustody for too long, inspectors find
OL,6,FMr Naylor said: "The staff we spoke to
OL,7,Fhighlighted that the custody division
OL,8,Faimed to minimise the number of child
OL,9,Farrests wherever possible, and to
OL,10,Freduce the time spent in custody at
OL,11,Fthe centres.
OL,13,F"However, our review of records
OL,14,Fhighlighted anomalies in the length of
OL,15,Ftime some children spent in custody.
