OL,3,CSeveral children detained in police
OL,4,Ccustody for too long, inspectors find
OL,6,F"We consider holding children in a
OL,7,Fcell for the length of times we noted
OL,8,Fto be inappropriate, disproportionate
OL,9,Fto the offence, inconsistent with
OL,10,Fcustody policy, and potentially
OL,11,Fdetrimental to the child.
OL,13,F"None of these records contained a
OL,14,Fsufficient rationale to explain why it
OL,15,Fwas necessary and proportionate to
OL,16,Fdelay liberating the child."
