OL,3,CSeveral children detained in police
OL,4,Ccustody for too long, inspectors find
OL,6,FShe said: "Whilst issues have been
OL,7,Fidentified and will be addressed, we
OL,8,Fhave seen a reduction in the number of
OL,9,Fyounger children being brought into
OL,10,Fcustody overall and a significant
OL,11,Fdecrease in the number of older
OL,12,Fchildren held over 24 hours.
OL,14,F"This demonstrates a collective desire
OL,15,Fnot to have children in our care for
OL,16,Fany longer than is absolutely
OL,17,Fnecessary, and this will continue to
OL,18,Fbe a priority for us.
